INSERT INTO public.site_content (key, value) VALUES
('city_gaithersburg_intro', 'Life in Gaithersburg moves between the buzz of the Kentlands, weekend strolls around Lakeforest, and quiet evenings off Quince Orchard. It''s a community that values its time — which is exactly what we give back. Between humid Mid-Atlantic summers that pull pollen and dust through every open window, salt and grit tracked in from winter commutes up I-270, and the relentless clay-tinged mud from Seneca Creek trails, even well-kept Gaithersburg homes need a thoughtful reset. Design Cleaning handles the details that pile up between soccer practice, biotech-corridor workdays, and family dinners — so your home feels calm the moment you walk in.'),
('city_washington-dc_intro', 'Living in DC means rowhouse charm in Capitol Hill, brunch in Shaw, and golden-hour walks along the Tidal Basin — but it also means tracked-in cherry blossom petals in spring, summer humidity that settles into upholstery, and the constant fine grit of a city under permanent construction. Whether you''re in a Logan Circle condo, a Georgetown townhouse, or a Navy Yard high-rise, the pace rarely slows. Design Cleaning takes the pressure off, working quietly around your schedule so you can spend less time scrubbing baseboards and more time enjoying the neighborhood you chose this city for.'),
('city_silver-spring_intro', 'Silver Spring blends downtown energy — the AFI, Sligo Creek concerts, the Saturday farmers market — with leafy, tree-lined streets that drop pollen, pine needles, and autumn debris straight onto your front step. Add humid Beltway summers, slushy winter walks from the Metro, and the everyday chaos of a community that''s always doing something, and even the most loved-in homes start to feel behind. Design Cleaning brings calm back to your space with the kind of detailed, considerate care that lets you fully enjoy what makes Silver Spring feel like home — without thinking about the dust on the ceiling fans.'),
('city_rockville_intro', 'Rockville pairs cultural richness — Rockville Town Square, the F. Scott Fitzgerald Theatre, Rock Creek''s wooded trails — with the everyday demands of a fast-moving Montgomery County lifestyle. Pollen-heavy springs coat windowsills, summer humidity invites dust to settle into rugs, and trails along Croydon Park or Cabin John mean muddy paws and gritty entryways year-round. Whether you''re in King Farm, Fallsmead, or a quiet pocket off Veirs Mill, your home deserves to feel like a retreat. Design Cleaning quietly handles every detail so you can spend your time on the things — and people — that actually matter.'),
('city_bethesda_intro', 'Bethesda rewards the people who live here — the restaurants along Bethesda Row, weekends on the Capital Crescent Trail, the easy NIH-and-downtown rhythm — but it also asks a lot of your time. Pollen rolls in heavy each spring, summer humidity dulls hardwood and glass, and trail dust and salt make their way inside no matter how careful you are. From Edgemoor estates to sleek downtown condos, Bethesda homes deserve the same quiet polish their owners bring to everything else. Design Cleaning delivers detail-obsessed, discreet service so you can simply enjoy your home — and your weekends — fully.'),
('city_germantown_intro', 'Germantown''s appeal is its balance — the trails at Black Hill Regional Park, the convenience of the Milestone shops, and quiet, family-friendly streets across Clopper Mill, Churchill, and Kingsview. But that same lifestyle invites mud from creekside walks, pollen drifting off the wooded edges of every neighborhood, and the steady wear of a household that''s always in motion. Design Cleaning steps in so your home feels effortlessly cared for — between school drop-offs, commutes down I-270, and the weekends you''d rather spend outdoors than scrubbing floors.')
